description: Data was loaded from the International Statistical Classification of Diseases and Related Health Problems 10th Revision published by the World Health Organization (WHO) in February 2019. More details: https://icd.who.int/browse10

fields.description: Level in the hierarchy. Usually 4, but sometimes 3
fields.name: hierarchy_level

fields.description: Leaf node type: X (explicitly listed in the classification) or S (derived from a subclassification)
fields.name: node_type

fields.description: Lowest 3-char code within this block.Examples: A15, A70, F90, G10
fields.name: min_block_number

fields.description: ICD-10 code. Example: C22.1 (If level is 3, code will have only two digits, e.g., C23)
fields.name: code

fields.description: ICD-10 code without the dot. Example: C221 (If level is 3, code will have only two digits, e.g., C23)
fields.name: code_nodot

fields.description: ICD-10 code title. Example: Malignant neoplasm: Intrahepatic bile duct carcinoma
fields.name: code_title
